CREATED:20240829T230534Z
DESCRIPTION:<table><tbody><tr><td><br><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><
 tr><td><br><p>Learn about how bike and scooter share services are affecting
  travel behavior and safety in and around the UC Davis campus.</p><p>Hope B
 odenschatz and Sampath Dangeti are graduate students at the UC Davis Instit
 ute of Transportation Studies. Hope will present the results of an experime
 nt that measured how the pricing of SPIN e-bikes and e-scooters impacted tr
 avel behavior. Sampath will present research on pedestrian and bicyclist sa
 fety on the UC Davis campus\, measured both with computer vision and throug
 h human observations.</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></tabl
 e></td></tr></tbody></table>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260308T023207Z
LOCATION:U.S. Bicycling Hall of Fame\, 303 3rd St\, Davis\, CA 95616\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:DBC Member Meeting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
