DTSTART:20250419T154500Z
DTEND:20250419T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260327T025937Z
UID:1dr6nkv8fumnjjcbgeqkud0r2d@google.com
CREATED:20250402T141522Z
DESCRIPTION:<br><br>Saturday\, April 19\, 2025 @8:45 AM<br><br><ul><li>Amtr
 ak train from Davis to Suisun</li><li>Return to Davis on bike via Pleasants
  Valley and Putah Creek</li><li>Cost is approximately $12 for a one-way tic
 ket from Davis to Suisun (can be purchased online prior to travel).</li><li
 >Train #729 departs Davis at 9:10 AM (I would think try to be there by 8:45
  for ticket purchase).</li><li>Arrives in Suisun/Fairfiled at 9:36 AM</li><
 li>Per Amtrak employee in the Davis station (and the Amtrak website)\, ther
 e should be enough bike storage spaces and there is no additional cost and 
 no reservation is required.</li><li>Bring a lock.</li><li>Returns to Davis 
 via Pleasants Valley and Putah Creek Road</li><li>Stop at Steady Eddy’s for
  a “coffee stop”</li><li>Please carry water\, food\, tools\, and appropriat
 e clothing.</li><li>Regroup as necessary</li><li>~15 miles per hour (or fas
 ter if the whole *GROUP* decides or the wind is giving a helping hand).</li
 ><li>This is not meant to be a fast ride and it is requested stronger rider
 s please support those that may need some assistance.</li><li>Plan for at l
 east 3 hours of actual ride time (this does not include "coffee stops" or t
 rain travel time).</li><li>~43 miles</li><li>About 1000 feet of total climb
 ing per RWGPS.</li><li>If you have a GPS\, please load the route before the
  ride.</li></ul><a href="https://www.strava.com/routes/3339441302072178054"
  target="_blank">https://www.strava.com/routes/<wbr />3339441302072178054</
 a><br><br>Carl Gilgut<br>(802) 233-2751
LAST-MODIFIED:20250402T141650Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Amtrak ride - Amtrak to Suisun - Return through Winters
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Davis Bike Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250215T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250215T120000
DTSTAMP:20260327T025937Z
UID:7rmkmovoe3l14a5833v4h6do8a@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250215T090000
CREATED:20241017T171351Z
DESCRIPTION:Time for some early season LSDs*. Tomorrow's 3rd Saturday  Ride
  will head northward toward Zamora and Dunnigan Hills via quiet country roa
 ds and Mary's Cemetery. Forecast looks to be a spectacular day for a bike r
 ide: sunny\, dry\, and light northerlies\, so we'll enjoy a gentle tailwind
  on the way home.<br>Pace will be a conversational double paceline where sa
 fe to do so\, 17-19mph. Possibly a little quicker on the return with the ta
 ilwind.<br><br>60 miles\, 720'<br><a href="https://ridewithgps.com/routes/4
 9719184" target="_blank">https://ridewithgps.com/routes<wbr />/49719184</a>
 <br><br>Ride Well. Do good things.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250505T005827Z
LOCATION:John Jones\, 2068 John Jones Rd\, Davis\, CA 95616\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:3rd Saturday Road Ride
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
