BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Davis Bike Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250419T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250419T160000
DTSTAMP:20260327T025937Z
UID:7rmkmovoe3l14a5833v4h6do8a@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250419T090000
CREATED:20241017T171351Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>How about <b>something different</b> on Saturday morning\, l
 ike a ride to East Nicolaus? Experience how flat the Sacramento Valley is: 
 the majority of the 'climbing' is between Davis and Woodland! Ace your next
  geography quiz by pinpointing Robbins on a map. We'll stop for lunch at th
 e iconic Sammie’s in E. Nicolaus\, which has great food and outdoor patio s
 eating. The return follows the beautiful Garden Highway for 35 uninterrupte
 d miles downstream along the Sacramento River all the way back to Old Sacra
 mento\, and passes Lauren Bacall and John Wayne's riverboat of 1955's "Bloo
 d Alley" fame\, the now high-and-dry "Spirit of Sacramento"! </p><p>As alwa
 ys\, group ride etiquette is expected and coached. A long-ish ride\, so we'
 ll keep the pace a bit slower than our typical\, especially for the first 2
 5miles\; and plan to let the stronger riders do more pulling so everyone st
 ays together for the duration. Plan to be self-sufficient with snacks\, dri
 nks\, tools\, etc. </p><p>For those who want <b>a shorter ride\, there are 
 options to turn back</b> anywhere on the north-bound leg\, or you can join 
 Carl Gilgut for his 'Train Ride' from Suisun (see DBC calendar).</p><p> </p
 ><p>Depart 0900 from business park just north of Starbucks on John Jones Rd
 . </p><p><u><a href="https://ridewithgps.com/routes/50345988" target="_blan
 k">https://ridewithgps.com/<wbr />routes/50345988</a></u></p><br>88miles\, 
 568' (NOT a typo)<br><p>Ride well. Do good things.</p><br><br><br>Robert-Ja
 n Enzerink
LAST-MODIFIED:20250505T005827Z
LOCATION:John Jones\, 2068 John Jones Rd\, Davis\, CA 95616\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:3rd Sat. - Unique\, 88 scenic and pancake-flat miles
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
