X-SOURCE:Davis Bike Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20251213T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20251213T130000
DTSTAMP:20260327T025937Z
UID:um3f9rrqc3e43vqnc0mj7nopip@google.com
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20251213T090000
CREATED:20251104T152227Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>The upcoming second Saturday ride will be a loop out of Mosk
 owite Corner (at the intersection of SR 121 and SR 128). Initially I was th
 inking of biking around Sutter Buttes\, but I think we will have a better c
 hance of seeing the sun if we get out of the Central Valley.</p><ul><li>Dat
 e: Second Saturday – December 13\, 2025<u></u><u></u></li><li>Start time: 9
 :30  a.m.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Start location: Moskowite Corner. Park at t
 he abandoned gas station at the west end of Steele Canyon Road\, not the la
 rge lot by the abandoned building.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Distance: 48 miles
 <u></u><u></u></li><li>Contact: Anne Huber\; <a href="mailto:anneh@dcn.org"
  target="_blank">anneh@dcn.org</a>\; 916-206-2922<u></u><u></u></li><li>Ser
 vices (Food\, water\, bathrooms): Food at Pope Valley Market at roughly mil
 e 28. Bring snacks. Restrooms: port-a-potty at Pope Valley Market.<u></u><u
 ></u></li><li>No need to RSVP<u></u><u></u></li><li>Rain cancellation or po
 stponement: would be communicated via the listserv.<u></u><u></u></li><li>P
 ace: 14 - 17 mph with regroups. The speed is meant to be an indicator of sp
 eed on flat terrain with no wind (although there is little flat terrain on 
 this ride). People can go faster if they want as long as they are willing t
 o regroup.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Route: <a href="https://ridewithgps.com/ro
 utes/35685887" target="_blank">https://ridewithgps.com/<wbr />routes/356858
 87</a><u></u><u></u></li></ul><p>This is a scenic\, hilly ride with 3\,200 
 feet of climbing<u></u><u></u></p><ul><li>For general information about the
  second Saturday ride and bicycling with the Davis Bike Club\, please see: 
 <a href="https://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-sat-explorer-ride/" target="_blank">
 https://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-<wbr />sat-explorer-ride/</a><u></u><u></u></
 li></ul><p>It includes the following: “Cycling has inherent risks. Any cycl
 ist taking part in a DBC ride releases DBC from any liability. Guests are w
 elcome to ride with DBC for one ride\; for subsequent rides\, you must be a
  member of the Club. By riding with a DBC group ride you acknowledge that y
 ou have read and understand this. Helmets are required on all rides.”</p><b
 r>Ride Description: <a href="https://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-sat-explorer-rid
 e/" target="_blank">https://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-sat-explorer-ride/</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260308T231507Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Second Saturday Explorer Ride
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
