DESCRIPTION:<p>Based on the NOAA forecast (<a href="https://www.cnrfc.noaa.
 gov/graphicalRVF.php?id=fmwc1" target="_blank">https://www.cnrfc.noaa.gov/<
 wbr />graphicalRVF.php?id=fmwc1</a>)\, it looks like water might still be f
 lowing from the Sacramento River over the Fremont Weir into the Yolo Bypass
  next Saturday\, so that’s where I would like to go for the January second 
 Saturday ride. The plan is to start at Woodland Nugget at 10:00 a.m.\, whic
 h should give people plenty of time to bike to the start if they choose. Br
 ing lunch or buy it at Nugget to eat at the weir. More info is below.<u></u
 ><u></u></p><p>If it turns out that the weir forecast changes and water is 
 no longer likely to be flowing over the weir on Saturday\, I’ll change the 
 route to be a loop to Matchbook Winery with the same start time and locatio
 n.<u></u><u></u></p><p>Please let me know if you need additional informatio
 n.<u></u><u></u></p><p>Thanks\,<u></u><u></u></p><p>-Anne<u></u><u></u></p>
 <p>(916) 206-2922</p><ul><li>Date: Second Saturday – January 10\, 2026<u></
 u><u></u></li><li>Start time: 10:00 a.m.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Start locati
 on: Woodland Nugget<u></u><u></u></li><li>Distance: 29 miles<u></u><u></u><
 /li><li>Contact: Anne Huber\; <a href="mailto:anneh@dcn.org" target="_blank
 ">anneh@dcn.org</a>\; 916-206-2922<u></u><u></u></li><li>Services (Food\, w
 ater\, bathrooms): bring food to eat at the Fremont Weir. Bathrooms might b
 e open at the park in Knights Landing<u></u><u></u></li><li>No need to RSVP
 <u></u><u></u></li><li>Rain cancellation or postponement: would be communic
 ated via the listserv.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Pace: 14 - 17 mph with regroup
 s. The speed is meant to be an indicator of speed on flat terrain with no w
 ind. People can go faster if they want as long as they are willing to regro
 up.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Route: <a href="https://ridewithgps.com/routes/53
 663927" target="_blank">https://ridewithgps.com/<wbr />routes/53663927</a><
 u></u><u></u></li></ul><p><u></u> <u></u></p><ul><li>For general informatio
 n about the second Saturday ride and bicycling with the Davis Bike Club\, p
 lease see: <a href="https://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-sat-explorer-ride/" targe
 t="_blank">https://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-<wbr />sat-explorer-ride/</a><u></
 u><u></u></li></ul><p>It includes the following: “Cycling has inherent risk
 s. Any cyclist taking part in a DBC ride releases DBC from any liability. G
 uests are welcome to ride with DBC for one ride\; for subsequent rides\, yo
 u must be a member of the Club. By riding with a DBC group ride you acknowl
 edge that you have read and understand this. Helmets are required on all ri
 des.”</p>
